highlights.text:
**South Africa's Dominant Win**

South Africa defeated Bangladesh by 149 runs in the 23rd match of the ICC Cricket World Cup 2023. Quinton de Kock scored 174 runs and Marco Jansen took 4 wickets for South Africa.

**Points Table Reshuffled**

South Africa moved to the second position with 8 points from 5 matches. India remained at the top with 10 points from 5 matches. Bangladesh stayed at the bottom with 2 points from 5 matches.

**Upcoming Matches**

The tournament is heating up as teams vie for the top four spots. South Africa, New Zealand, and Australia are in contention, while India is the frontrunner. Bangladesh faces a tough challenge in their remaining matches.

cards.abstract: PM Narendra Modi said that India worships Shakti (Mata Durga) not for itself but for the welfare, well-being and prosperity of the whole universe.

images.title: PM Narendra Modi Takes Veiled Dig At China, Says 'Shastra Puja In India...'

highlights.text:
**PM Modi's speech on Dussehra:**

- **Veiled dig at China:** PM Modi said that India worships weapons to protect its land and not to capture other lands, in an apparent reference to China's expansionist policy.
- **India's philosophy and ideology:** PM Modi said that India worships Shakti for the welfare of the whole universe and knows the teachings of Geeta as well as the manufacturing of INS Vikrant and Tejas. He said that India respects Shri Ram and also knows how to protect its borders.
- **Alert against divisive forces:** PM Modi said that the burning of Ravana should also burn the elements that threaten the harmony of the society and the powers who want to divide India on the basis of caste and religion. He also indirectly attacked Congress over its caste census demand.

cards.title: BlackRock CEO Larry Fink, world’s biggest money manager with over $9 tn in assets, flies to India to meet Mukesh Ambani
cards.abstract: Larry Fink, the world's largest asset manager with over $9 trillion in assets, recently undertook a brief visit to India to meet his business partner, Mukesh Ambani. In Mumbai, Fink toured the expansive Jio Campus in Navi Mumbai and RIL's high-end retail hub in the Bandra Kurla Complex.

images.title: BlackRock CEO Larry Fink, world’s biggest money manager with over $9 tn in assets, flies to India to meet Mukesh Ambani

highlights.text: The article reports on ***Larry Fink's*** visit to India to meet his business partner, **Mukesh Ambani**, and discuss their joint venture in **digital asset management**. Fink, the world's largest asset manager with over **$9 trillion** in assets, toured the **Jio Campus** in Navi Mumbai and the **Bandra Kurla Complex** retail hub, and met with **Prime Minister Narendra Modi** in New Delhi. He also highlighted **BlackRock's** significant presence and role in India, and praised **Reliance's** impressive digital and consumer ecosystem, unmatched elsewhere in the world. The joint venture, announced in July, involves each partner investing up to **$150 million** in a 50:50 partnership to launch a **digital-first asset management platform** for the growing investor base in India. The timing of the visit, just before the **COP28 summit** in Dubai next month, carries significance as both Reliance and BlackRock advocate for the **clean energy agenda**, with Ambani announcing in 2021 that all Reliance businesses will achieve **net-zero carbon emissions** by 2035.
